Meeting the Winnower<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
The room Selilya has designated to meet Xosha in was functional, and just on the poorer side of uncomfortable. Selilya sat in a tall wooden chair, the back reaching past her head as she sat. The chair had no cushions and seemed even un sanded and rough to Xosha's appraisal. The table she sat before was much the same, though not roughy so much now as uneven. The surface of the table waving and bucking to knots in the wood. <br>
<br>
There was two other pieces of furniture in the room, the short stool that sat opposite Selilya, clearly for Xosha to sit on (also clear was the the stool had been made shorter than the Winnower's chair for a reason, if Xosha sat in it, her knees would bend up to her chest, and she would be sitting mucyh lower than the other woman, giving Xosha's questionner a much more powerful seating during the meeting), and a candelabra directly behind Selilya, creating a dark shadow over her face, the dramatic effect surprised even Xosha. <br>
<br>
&quot;Good of you to come, young assassin.&quot; Selilya spoke not in words it seemed, but rather the sound of her speach seemed intoned as bells ringing and echoing. <br>
<br>
Xosha sighed, she seemed to always be called young, or child, it was a throw over from her apprenticeship. As tradition stated, the teacher, despite age, would always be the senior of the two, and to show the differentiation from teacher and student (and Xo suspected, also to keep the apprentice from getting a full head) the student was always referred to in reflection to this. Child or young one, even analgies like sapling and spark were common. Sadly, before Xosha could take an apprentice of her own, her Il-Haress had passed, and Xo feared that without her master's example, the term would stick. <br>
<br>
&quot;Of course Winnower, that is how they call you?&quot; Xosha asked slyly. Selilya nodded, the expression on her face hidden by shadow. &quot;more than a few people tell me that your group is a powerful force in the taking of the lands for Innoruuk.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Then am I to understand that you study our group?&quot; Selilya sounded light and easy with these words, they trickled in the room as fairy bells and tinkling pixie charms. <br>
<br>
Xosha grinned. &quot;I have watched a few, even gotten my hands on a copy of your.... constitution... shall we call it?&quot; Xosha gambled here. To admit to having access to private goods of the guild is might anger this leader, but also it seemed necessary for Xo to make a point, especially since she had certain aims in this guild all ready, and needed to show at least some of her abilities right off. <br>
<br>
Luck was with Xo, for Selilya chuckled, her bell like tone going deep now and powerful. &quot;I would expect nothing less of one with your past, I also have heard some of your history. Killed two teachers at the Ebon Mask, apprenticed quickly out of that thieves school in the very moment you were to be executed...&quot; <br>
<br>
Very well, thought Xo, I have shown you that I am wise in the mention of your guild charter, and you have shown that I am weak, with example of my capture and need for salvation... back to square one... <br>
<br>
&quot;Winnower, this would go nowhere if we continued to parlay gently and size eachother up with verbal hooks and catches. To see this 'child' for what she is, you will need to see her in action, I take it that for membership there is some grand quest I must accomplish for you?&quot; <br>
<br>
Selilya turned her head just slightly to the side, her left eye now being visible in the light of the candle, Xosha saw her amusment therein. &quot;Is there not always?&quot; <br>
<br>
Xosha smiled, now we were getting somewhere. Perhaps you don't see it yet Winnower, but THIS assassin will be the strongest ally you have ever gained. And I think I may gain something from you, if my instincts on the posibilites of your people are near correct. <br>
<br>
&quot;Well then Winnower, what can I do for you?&quot; <br>
<br>
