Re: Meeting the Winnower<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Selilya had mentioned to Naedra, her assistant, that she would be in the research room upstairs reviewing more pieces of scrolls that had been discovered in her last trip to Permafrost. She went to the unfinished room from time to time when members of the Harvest would return to the grange for rest, refreshment, and reporting to superiors. Her office was not far from the main hall, and although the din of voices usually didn't bother her, there were still some moments when concentration was harder to maintain. This would result in a retreat to the study upstairs. <br>
<br>
Before long, Naedra escorted the rogue, Xosha, to the study. Selilya had heard her name mentioned by several of her peers and was quite pleased this one had sought out the Violent Harvest. With the impending wars ahead, having one with the gift of evasion and stealth would be most valuable. <br>
<br>
&quot;Good of you to come, young assassin,&quot; Selilya smiled. She knew that the next few moments of conversation would consist of the usual posturing and sizing up. That didn't bother Selilya...she was used to it. Her role as part zealot and part diplomat gave her many opportunities to indulge in this exercise. <br>
<br>
Eventually the matter of the entrance requirements to the grange was discussed. Xosha had done her research well and knew of the &quot;quest&quot; to be completed before she would earn her membership in the order. <br>
<br>
&quot;Well then Winnower, what can I do for you?&quot; Xosha inquired. <br>
<br>
Selilya sat back and smiled at Xosha. She had already been thinking of a challenge for the rogue...a measure of her abilities. A highly skilled assassin should be able to go practically anywhere at anytime to accomplish a mission. <br>
<br>
&quot;There is an Erudite witch named Maugarim who has taken an icon needed by our clerics. The reports I have heard indicate she may have fled to Kerra Island. I want you to track her down, Xosha. Hunt her down and punish her for her actions. Our clerics are far to important to be treated this way. Now, I'd like you to take at least one travelling companion...more if you wish...from our order. Show them this missive, so they will have no doubt that your &quot;trip&quot; has been commissioned by me. Good hunting, young assassin. From all I've been told about you, you should have no trouble.&quot; <br>
<br>
Selilya arose from her chair and handed Xosha a scroll closed with the Winnower's seal. As she began to walk by, she placed her hand on Xosha's shoulder. <br>
<br>
&quot;Your mentor was something special, Xosha. We, as the Chosen race, mourn her passing. She believed in you, I know. I, too, expect great things from you.&quot; <br>
<br>
Selilya walked out into the hall, leaving the young assassin to her thoughts. <br>
